stricted level: check_seccompProfile_restricted.go implements CheckSeccompProfileRestricted() which requires a seccomp profile to be set and only allows RuntimeDefault or Localhost types.\n\n**Core API Validation** in pkg/apis/core/validation/validation.go implements:\n- ValidateSecurityContext(): validates SecurityContext fields including privileged flag and capabilities restrictions\n- validateSeccompProfileField(): validates seccomp profile configuration\n- validatePodSpecSecurityContext(): validates pod-level security context including seccomp profiles\n\nThese validation layers work together to enforce Kubernetes Pod Security Standards through the admission controller plugin (plugin/pkg/admission/security/podsecurity/admission.go) which delegates to the upstream pod-security-admission library (staging/src/k8s.io/pod-security-admission/) for policy evaluation and enforcement."
